    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Mana sphere.</p>\n<p><strong>Benefit:</strong> Whenever you use an (expunge) talent on a creature that can use spells or sphere effects, you can spend an additional spell point to destabilize their magic, causing them to have a 20% chance to trigger a wild magic event every time they use magic. The target gets a Will save against your Mana sphere DC to resist this effect, and it lasts for a number of rounds equal to your casting ability modifier. The chance to trigger a wild magic event increases by 10% per additional wild magic feat you possess, to a maximum chance of 60%.</p>\n<p>For information regarding wild magic events and the wild magic system, see <a href=\"/wild-magic\">Wild Magic</a> by Drop Dead Studios.</p>\n",
